Many free note-taking applications offer robust checklist functionality to help you stay organized. Here are some of the top options:

*   **Google Keep** is a lightweight and user-friendly app ideal for quick notes, checklists, and reminders across various devices. It allows you to create checklists, color-code notes, add labels, and set time or location-based reminders. Google Keep also offers real-time syncing and collaboration features.
*   **Microsoft OneNote** provides a flexible and free platform for structured note-taking across Windows, macOS, iOS, Android, and the web. You can organize notes into notebooks, sections, and pages, and it supports typing, handwriting, drawing, inserting images, and recording audio.